Three night guards at the Kivaywa Boys High School in Lugari were ambushed and killed by armed criminals on Wednesday night. The attackers also made off with several computers and a television set, according to Matete OCPD Thomas Ototo, who confirmed the Wednesday night incident. The bodies of the security guards which had deep cuts were discovered scattered throughout the school area, according to the authorities. According to the police chief, an investigation into the matter has begun, and the bodies of the deceased have been moved to the Lugari funera home. More to followâ€¦ Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys